    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a concours-level 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, a definitive example of the 996.2 generation. This widebody 4S maintains its factory-specified M96 3.6-liter naturally aspirated flat-six, delivering 315 horsepower through a precise 6-speed manual transaxle and an advanced viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system. Mechanically, this unit is impeccable, featuring a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recently refreshed cooling system with a low-temperature thermostat. The suspension geometry remains true to factory tolerances, utilizing the stiffer Turbo-spec chassis and Big Red four-piston monobloc Brembo calipers over cross-drilled rotors. Zero deferred maintenance, no bore scoring, and a pristine DME overrev report. This is a turn-key investment for the discerning purist seeking peak analog performance.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
