    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a collector-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, preserved in its purest form. This specimen features the iconic 13B-REW twin-rotor engine, utilizing its original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration for seamless boost transition. The power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis remains a benchmark in balance, boasting a 50/50 weight distribution and a sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension system that provides surgical turn-in. This vehicle has undergone a comprehensive mechanical audit, confirming optimal compression across all rotor faces and zero vacuum leaks within the complex 'rat's nest' solenoid rack. The exterior retains its factory luster with no evidence of panel misalignment or paint degradation, while the cockpit is free of the typical plastics fatigue common to this era. A rare, turnkey investment for the rotary purist.",
